HEADWORD: Piecer
<hw>Pie"cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
pieces; a patcher.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A child employed in spinning mill to tie together
broken threads.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piecework</ent>⟦br⟧
